flowRoot.flowPara: This isn't very enthusiastic, positive or encouraging.
Sounds a bit downbeat or ironic. The call to action should be more assertive: "Pick an area", "Find a task", ...
Double links create uncertainy and put a burden on the visitor. Each area should have one link only.
Visual style of links isn't inviting. You should want to click them!
This section feels like an afterthought. It's unstructured and isn't clear how it relates to the core message (if you can find it!) Small print is a distraction.
Be a part of a vibrant worldwide community
GNOME is a friendly and welcoming community. Contributing is a great way to learn skills, gain experience, have fun, and help to create world-class Free Software.
Find a bug that suits you: we have every kind. We also have an excellent newcomers guide to help you get started.
Write user and developer documention with our active documentation team.
The Engagement Team works on marketing, user outreach, events organisation, and websites.
GNOME is translated into over 80 languages, all thanks to our volunteers. Help to translate it into your language!
Be a part of a vibrant worldwide community
GNOME is a friendly and welcoming community. Getting involved is a great way to learn skills, have fun, and help to create world-class Free Software. Join us!
GNOME has every kind of coding task. We also have guides to help you get started.
Write user and developer documention with our active documentation team.
The Engagement Team works on marketing, user outreach, events organisation, and websites. It wants your help!
GNOME is translated into over 80 languages, all thanks to our volunteers. Help to translate it into your language!
Can't find what you're looking for?
There are many other teams and activities in the GNOME project, including testing, design, bug triage, system administration, and more.
Lacks a human dimension or friendliness. Where are the people?
Simple and easy to understand. Not too many words.
Point to the best places for new contributors. Don't be encyclopedic.
